	<div class="container">
		<div class="project-hero__content">
			
			<h1 class="project-hero__title">Mental health care outcry targets Kaiser — and state regulators</h1>

			
						<p class="project-hero__intro">Striking clinicians — spotlighting complaints that patients with serious mental illness face long waits and inadequate care — lay blame at the doorstep of the state Department of Managed Health Care.</p>
			
							<div class="project-hero__caption">

											<svg role="img" class="icon icon--camera" aria-label="camera"><use xlink:href="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/themes/thenewsproject/dist/svg/dist/symbol/svg/sprite.symbol.svg#camera"></use></svg>						<span>Dozens of mental healthcare workers picket outside of Sacramento Medical Center to protest long wait times for patients and overwhelming case-loads at Kaiser Permanente facilities. Photo by Anne Wernikoff for CalMatters</span>
									</div>
					</div>
	</div>
</div>

